# 🌊 Rising Waters – Flood Prediction using Machine Learning

## 📌 Project Overview

Floods are among the most destructive natural disasters, causing significant loss of life, property, and infrastructure every year. Timely prediction of flood events enables authorities to issue early warnings, organize evacuations, and allocate emergency resources efficiently.

**Rising Waters** is a Machine Learning-based Flood Prediction System that analyzes historical rainfall and seasonal weather patterns to classify whether a flood is likely to occur. Multiple machine learning algorithms are trained and compared, with **XGBoost** selected as the best-performing model for deployment.

The trained model is integrated into a Flask web application, making flood risk prediction simple, scalable, and suitable for deployment on cloud platforms such as IBM Cloud.

---

# 🎯 Objectives

* Analyze historical rainfall data.
* Perform comprehensive Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA).
* Identify important rainfall patterns related to flood occurrence.
* Train multiple classification models.
* Compare model performances.
* Select and save the best-performing model.
* Integrate the trained model into a Flask web application.
* Enable cloud deployment for real-time flood prediction.

---

# 📂 Dataset

The dataset contains historical rainfall records and flood occurrence information.

### Features

| Feature   | Description                               |
| --------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| YEAR      | Year of observation                       |
| JAN – DEC | Monthly rainfall                          |
| Jan-Feb   | Seasonal rainfall (January–February)      |
| Mar-May   | Seasonal rainfall (March–May)             |
| Jun-Sep   | Monsoon rainfall                          |
| Oct-Dec   | Post-monsoon rainfall                     |
| ANNUAL    | Total annual rainfall                     |
| FLOODS    | Target variable (0 = No Flood, 1 = Flood) |

